docs.abstract: Even as the Kate Spade brand passed from owner to owner, shoppers never stopped associating the company with Ms. Spade, and Ms. Spade with good style.
docs.snippet: Even as the Kate Spade brand passed from owner to owner, shoppers never stopped associating the company with Ms. Spade, and Ms. Spade with good style.
docs.lead_paragraph: Soon after fans of Kate Spade learned that the designer had died in an apparent suicide on Tuesday, stunned customers remembered the handbags they purchased after their first big promotion, or the linens they were given for their first home, or the onesies in which they dressed their babies.

headline.main: Kate Spade and Fashion’s Identity Crisis: When a Name Makes a Brand
headline.print_headline: When the Name Leaves the Namesake

docs.abstract: Johnson & Johnson must pay damages to women who claimed that asbestos in talcum powder products caused them to develop ovarian cancer.

docs.abstract: The company added more than 100,000 digital-only subscribers in the second quarter, enough to make up for a continued decline in advertising revenue.
